<p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uastaliashadowflame.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Astalia Shadowflame</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/8/00 6:38:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Quests</span><hr size=1> Band of Rodcet Nife.<br>3 int 10 mana lore noddrop ring.  (Still using it at 38 as 200 int is real easy to get and the mana is nice)<br>Qeynos quest<br>Boost faction by doing blessed oil/Prayer beads quests. (Easy) Till you can get the quest for band.<br>You will lose faction with Bloodsabers.. Gain faction with Temple of life.<br>Make a Newbie fish killer.. (To take nasty faction hit)<br>Level him up to level 3 or so. (You don't lose exp for death at that level and it may be faster than healing so keep your newbie weapon.  It will stay with you when you die.)<br>Kill Kolandil fish in pond When a Kolandil fish appears on corpse..  Log out fish killer and In with your selected character.  Loot fish.. Hand fish in and pray you get it. Repeat as many times as necessary.<br>MEGA faction hits for this (Both ways) I was unlucky and got ring at about 6th or 7th fish ?9? got me to warmly with Temple of life I think.  I think I stopped at ?12 or 13?  Fast and easy faction with Temple of life vs local pirate lowlife faction I guess.<br><br><br>Word of warning.<br>The one blacksmith shop between bank  and lion's mane is Bloodsabers faction  (KOS by shopkeeper). stay out after that.<br>Also.. In the sewers..  Guys down there are Bloodsabers.<br>The guys by the shark pond are bloodsabers faction. ( Re: Staff of the wheel quest)<br>Invis and grab rod and be invis before going in or out or they will thump ya.<br><br>Bloodsabers are insignifigant enough to not worry much about this quest IMHO.<br><br>Golden Ear stud quest in Qeynos is good too.  +3int Earrings...<br>Legionaire Shoulderpads (From crushbone -&gt;Kaladim is a good quest to boost faction with dwarves.<br>Thats about all that comes to mind<br>I recommend not doing Gatecaller gloves quest as Heretics will hate you and Paineel will become off limits.<br>Thats about it (Off the top of my head) for low level wizard quests that I would deem worthwhile, though any quests that boost factions without side affects are good.<br> <p>Astalia Shadowflame <BR>Wizard of the 38'th ascension.<BR>Solusek Ro <BR><BR>- The power has always been there... <BR>Perception and control are limits you've placed on yourself.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchasryan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>chasryan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/9/00 9:40:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> start a SK</span><hr size=1> if you do the band of rodcet nife quest and start a new char to kill the fish, start a shadowknight, because they get harm touch which makes it really easy to kill the fish <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=83.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=83.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.e